        <div class="body">
            <p>Having a clear use case is important, but as a side comment I want to point out that although one could write a solution as follows with no "hooks":</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class MyTable extends Zend_Db_Table_Abstract
{
  public function __construct($options)
  {
    // pre-init code
    parent::__construct($options);
    // post-init code
  }
}
</code></pre>

<p>However, "Call Super" is considered an anti-pattern:  <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_super">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_super</a></p>

